CatDescriptText: Mrs. Betty White, transcribing typist, 1544 Oberlin Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 22, 1959, pg. A1 with question: "Do you think that the visit of the Russian ruler, Khrushchev, will promote world peace?" answer reads: "It should if there is mutual understanding."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Betty White wearing sleeveless floral dress with narrow belt and eyeglasses, standing under Jenkins Arcade marquee, Liberty Avenue, Downtown
